Aim

To estimate probability of occurrence as a function of distance to closest related species. I have done this in a normal ML framework (below), but i have aggregate all species together. This is unfair since each species has a different pattern of relatedness in the phylogeny. Comparing relatedness of 0.2 is different between brilliants (many closely related speices) and patagona (few closely related species). I still want to estimate a single model, so species slopes will be drawn in a hiericichal manner. I believe the model should be polynomial


Model Formulation

Our ultimate goal is: \[ y \sim dbern(p) \]

\[ logit(p) = \alpha_{species} + \beta_{species} *x + \gamma_{species} *x^2 \]

\[ \text{where} \: \alpha, \: \beta, \: \gamma \: \text{for each species are} \sim dnorm(\mu,\tau) \]

\[ \text{p is the probability of presence at a site}\] \[ \text{x= distance to a closely related species }\]

I will proceed slowly increasing in model complexity.

#Load if needed

dpars<-dcast(pars,...~parameter)

#sample 1000 values
samp<-dpars[sample(1:nrow(dpars),1000),]

traj<-list()
for(x in 1:nrow(samp)){
  s<-samp[x,]
  p<-inv.logit(s$alpha + s$beta* dat$value +s$gamma * dat$value^2)
  traj[[x]]<-data.frame(x=dat$value,y=p,Iteration=x)
}
    traj<-rbind_all(traj)

#summarise mean and interval
mtraj<-group_by(traj,x) %>% summarise(mean=mean(y),upper=quantile(y,0.975),lower=quantile(y,0.025))

ggplot(mtraj,aes(x=x,y=mean)) + geom_line(col="red",linetype="dashed") + geom_line(aes(y=upper),col="blue",linetype="dashed") + geom_line(aes(y=lower),col="blue",linetype="dashed")+ theme_bw() + labs(x="Phylogenetic distance to closest related species in an assemblage",y="Probability of occurrence")

#Load if needed

dpars<-dcast(pars,...~parameter)

#sample 1000 values
samp<-dpars[sample(1:nrow(dpars),1000),]

traj<-list()
for(x in 1:nrow(samp)){
  s<-samp[x,]
  p<-inv.logit(rnorm(1,mean=s$intercept,sd=s$sigmaIntercept) + s$beta* dat$value +s$gamma * dat$value^2)
  traj[[x]]<-data.frame(x=dat$value,y=p,Iteration=x)
}
    traj<-rbind_all(traj)

#summarise mean and interval
mtraj<-group_by(traj,x) %>% summarise(mean=mean(y),upper=quantile(y,0.975),lower=quantile(y,0.025))

ggplot(mtraj,aes(x=x,y=mean)) + geom_line(col="red",linetype="dashed") + geom_line(aes(y=upper),col="blue",linetype="dashed") + geom_line(aes(y=lower),col="blue",linetype="dashed")+ theme_bw() + labs(x="Phylogenetic distance to closest related species in an assemblage",y="Probability of occurrence")

Model Fitting - Varying Intercept and Slope

\[ y \sim dbern(p) \]

\[ logit(p) = \alpha_{Species} + \beta_{Species} *x + \gamma_{Species} *x^2 \] \[ \alpha_{Species} \sim N(intercept,sigmaIntercept)\] \[ \beta_{Species} \sim N(slope,sigmaSlope)\] \[ \gamma_{Species} \sim N(slope2,sigmaSlope2)\]

## [16]     }
